Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE Large Format Retail is pleased to present as the exclusive agents the Sunbury Showrooms development at 85 Vineyard Road, Sunbury.

The site is currently occupied by Bunnings Warehouse and is situated on the corner of Vineyard and McDougall Road, When Bunnings Warehouse relocates to the southern side of McDougall Road and begins trading in June 2014, the Sunbury Showrooms will be converted to approximately 6,026sqm of floor space, potentially across 6 tenancies.

- Approximately 18,600 vehicles passing the site daily.
- The Sunbury Showrooms will be the only dedicated homemaker centre in Sunbury.
- Access to over 140 car bays (2.3 car spaces per 100sqm)
- An estimated catchment of over 77,000 people.
- Bulky Goods Spending Rates higher than Melbourne averages
- Signalised intersection on Vineyard Road
- Strategic position adjacent to a new Bunnings Warehouse

Brand new freestanding service station in one of Melbourne's fastest growing residential suburbs with Sunbury set to grow by 66% between 2018 and 2041

Strategic main road site of 2,023sqm* with exposure to over 20,000 passing cars daily

Brand new 15 year NET lease to international fuel retailer Puma Energy who have over 270 retail sites and 20 depots across Australia

Significant tax saving depreciation benefits through brand new improvements

The first service station and convenience retail store on the main road into Sunbury providing excellent access and exposure

Highly attractive fixed annual rental increases of 3%

Net annual income of $283,010*
